In addition, I have installed an aftermarket single point sling adapter (way better than the OEM janky one). It also has a Levang Linear Compensator installed. title: For Sale:  These 4 listings are all a scam
postcontent:
For your viewing pleasure, 4 excellent examples of a scam. The pictures are all pulled from the internet, gunbroker, ar15.com, etc... If you click on listings by this user you can see all the firearms he's "selling". The easiest way to find out if it's probably a scam is to highlight the title of an ad then cut and paste it in to a google search. Chances are you will find the exact pictures on gunbroker, gunsinternational.com or gunauction.com. Armslist is a fantastic community but you need to protect yourself. If someone won't meet you ftf, show ID or right you a bill of sale walk away. Don't deal with someone who requires you to mail payment. You can cut and paste these auctions in to the browser for viewing. By the way the legitimate seller of the .260 has it listed on gunbroker.
